# CP/M disk-image geometry database (cpmtools `diskdefs` format) — DR-048.
#
# Bundled with cpm-fm for auto-detecting the geometry of a raw-sector CP/M image
# (FR-170). Each `diskdef <name> ... end` stanza gives the sector size, track and
# sector counts, allocation block size, directory size, sector skew, and number
# of reserved/boot tracks. Users may point cpm-fm at their own diskdefs file.
#
# The RomWBW (wbw_*) and RC2014 definitions below are taken verbatim from the
# RomWBW v3.6 `Source/Images/diskdefs` so cpm-fm recognises the standard RomWBW
# floppy and hard-disk images (fd144/fd120/fd720/fd360, hd1k, hd512) and the
# Grant Searle RC2014 CompactFlash slice. The generic floppies are the canonical
# cpmtools layouts.

# --- Generic CP/M floppies ---------------------------------------------------

# IBM 3740 8" SSSD — the reference CP/M floppy (250 KiB).
diskdef ibm-3740
  seclen 128
  tracks 77
  sectrk 26
  blocksize 1024
  maxdir 64
  skew 6
  boottrk 2
  os 2.2
end

# Osborne 1 5.25" SSDD (100 KiB).
